As of 3bc73cc7683a927374f0f72be4185e41f9e1cfed this throws an internal error:

```systemverilog
package pkg;
  class cls;
    bit a;
    rand bit b;
    constraint c {
      if (a) b dist {1 := 1, 0 := 0  };
    }
    function int f();
        void'(this.randomize());
    endfunction
  endclass
endpackage

module top;
endmodule
```

```
%Error: Internal Error: disterr.sv:6:16: ../V3Randomize.cpp:2238: Visit function missing? Constraint function missing for math node: DIST 0x600001089e00 {e6aq} u1=0x1 @dt=0x600001488600@(G/w1)
    6 |       if (a) b dist {1 := 1, 0 := 0  };
      |                ^~~~
```

Prior to that it used to throw `CONSTRAINTIGN` which could be ignored.

@YilouWang

